Results.ReviewText: I'm so glad I picked up a jar of be nescafe instant it's smooth warming blend was very refreshing. It really awakens your senses as smell of it hits you and the it's warm smooth texture was excerlant. I wasn't going to but but once I saw the lovely girl in Tesco advertising I decided to give it a go and I must say I'd buy again! Well done nescafe you did it and made the ultimate blend!
Results.Title: Smooth and awakening

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks very much for letting us know your thoughts on the new recipe. It's sad to hear you're not a fan but we really appreciate your feedback! The residue you can see at the bottom of your cup is micro ground coffee that was added to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend during the recent change. This is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee!

Results.ReviewText: I've used Gold Blend coffee for years and it's always been our household favourite by a long stretch. The new recipe just isn't as good by a long stretch. The rich aroma has gone and the taste isn't as good, and like others have said, the new stuff leaves a grotty sludge in the bottom of the cup. It tastes like a supermarket poor imitation of the original Gold Blend. So disappointed.
Results.Title: Bring back the original Gold Blend

Results.ReviewText: This delicious gold blend is a favourite in our house. We love taking ten minutes to sit down, relax and savour a nice hot cup of it with our feet up. I must say, the jar also seems to be more rounded than other brands and stylish too, so it goes well with our modern house! Having this coffee brings us back to reality during a busy day, just the smell of it is wonderful. We love it!
Results.Title: The Classic - What more could we need!

Results.ReviewText: Nescafé Gold Blend is the ONLY coffee I woukd buy but since the change I no longer enjoy it as much. The most negative aspect being the fact that sediment now seems to settle making the coffee taste bitter rather than smooth. So disappointed with the change and believe you me..I drink enough to give a well tested review. Please reconsider the change to this once smooth silky coffee.
Results.Title: Not the same!

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks very much for your review. After receiving feedback, we've added micro ground coffee to our blend, to give it a richer aroma whilst maintaining the same smoothness. It's disappointing to hear you don't enjoy the changes we've made. Your comments have been noted and shared with the rest of the team. If you still have your receipt for the jars you've recently purchased we're sure the store would be happy to refund you.

Results.ReviewText: We like a strong coffee and have used Gold Blend for countless years and thoroughly enjoyed every cup. Unfortunately, we purchased a load of the newly branded Gold Blend and hate it. I now have 10 x 200g jars and 7 x 275g refills to use. The taste is very bitter and the residue in the bottom of the cup is not pleasant. Why did you have to mess about with something that was good?
Results.Title: New Branding, awful taste

Results.ReviewText: I bought the coffee a few weeks back, thinking of trying something different as I always buy the original Nescafe, and i can say, hands down, one of the best coffees i have ever had. However, the downside is that it is a little bit mild for my taste, it needs a tiny bit more flavour as if you add any syrup to it, the taste is drowned out, however, other than that, it is divine.
Results.Title: Amazing taste

Results.ReviewText:
Been drinking NescafeGold a Blend since I arrived in UK from Malaysia.
Being from Malacca, Malaysia, my relatives own most of the famous ground factory. Thus, coffee has been my first cup of hot drink since I was a child.
I tried other brand of coffee, including Nescafe coffee but Nescafe Gold is still my ideal Cuppa for 41 years! What more can I say, Rich, Smooth and Black!
Results.Title: My Instant Comfort!

Results.ReviewText: I normally buy coffee from a well known shop on my way to work but to give me a few more moments in bed, and cut back on costs, I decided to make an instant coffee to take. I went for a trusty brand; Nescafe Gold Blend. Glad I did. Great taste and great value; for the cost of two days take out coffee I can buy a large jar and still have a great tasting cup of coffee for weeks.
Results.Title: Great coffee.

Results.ReviewText: I used to drink Maxwell House for years and year, but my husband got me this when I sent him to the shops, I ranted and raved until I tasted this beautiful coffee. I no longer have Maxwell House in the house. I find Nescafe Gold Blend has the taste I want, nice and smooth, not strong, it wakes me up in the morning and keeps me going all day at work as I bring my own jar in.
Results.Title: Great Taste

ClientResponses.Response: It's really sad to hear you're not a fan of the changes we've made but thank you for taking the time & letting us know!

Results.ReviewText: I have drunk Gold Blend for as long as I can remember and always enjoyed it. I could not believe the insipid flavour and the bitter dregs in the bottom of the cup with the new version. At first I thought I had bought a bad batch until I looked into it online. I found some old stock in a local shop and it was as delicious as ever! I will not be buying the new version again.
Results.Title: Why the change?

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, it's really sad to hear you're not a fan of the changes we've made recently! We're always wanting our consumers to have the best experience, therefore we've added micro ground coffee to our NESCAFÉ Gold Blend to give it a richer aroma while also maintaining the same smoothness. Thank you for taking the time to let us know. We've made a note of your comments & will pass them to the rest of the team.

Results.ReviewText: I'm another customer that has been using Gold Blend for over 20 years but not any more. I am fussy about my coffee and would carry some with me when out visiting but this new blend isn't nice at all. I didn't want a barista experience, I wanted the lovely coffee I've been so used to. Why fix something that ain't broke? I'm looking for an alternative, I'm so sad about this.
Results.Title: So disappointed

Results.ReviewText:
Purchased a couple of weeks ago not realising it was not my usual blend.
Taste - a slightly sharper taste, so I use a little less coffee..  It leaves a darkish residue which is visible at the bottom of the mug. I am now used to the new flavour,  I will purchase again but prefer the original. 
New design jar is more attractive and the new style lid is much easier to open.
Results.Title: Sleeker design.

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks very much for letting us know your thoughts on the new recipe. We really appreciate your feedback! The residue you can see at the bottom of your cup is micro ground coffee that was added to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend during the recent change. This is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee!

Results.ReviewText: Sorry, but right from the minute you open the lid and smell the coffee you can tell it's different from the previous blend. the smell is harsher, not as sweet..as is the taste. It also leaves a dark residue at the bottom of the cup.  Gold Blend has always been my choice for years..but now I will have to look for another brand. Sorry but this is not the Gold Blend I like.
Results.Title: Not as good as previous Gold Blend

Results.ReviewText: What can I say that has not been said before ? I go into coffee shops and the have a large range Expresso Lati da ect and all I want is Nescafe Gold Blend and they go WHAT ! so I now carry a small amount about my person and just ask for hot water and I do not care about the way they look at me because I like your coffee for its taste ,its quality ,and what I ;like !!!!
Results.Title: BEST IN THE WEST

ClientResponses.Response: It saddens us to hear you're not happy with the changes we've made but we really appreciate your feedback! Thank you for getting in touch & letting us know.

Results.ReviewText: Bought this not realising this coffee had been changed. Nescafe Gold Blend is the only brand l have always stayed loyal too. So my disappointment was off the scale.  I always look forward to popping the foil and smelling the aroma. That was the first sign things had changed. Taste was next. How could  something so lovely been so spoilt. No longer on my shopping list.
Results.Title: Really disappointed

ClientResponses.Response: We're certainly making a note of all comments around these changes so thank you for leaving your feedback.

Results.ReviewText: Only 1 star, a zero stars cant be done. Weaker coffee with sludge in the cup. Not a very pleasing coffee experience. Using last of the 'old' recipe before moving on to a different brand - UNLESS YOU SEE YOUR ERROR AND CHANGE IT BACK. Please listen to your reviews - this was once a very nice coffee. We have bought for 20 years - that looks like it will end soon
Results.Title: Poor poor taste

Results.ReviewText: I tried this a month ago and it is my new favourite brew! I just love the flavour and I think it is fantastic value for money. I used to buy the barista style instant which although lovely, tend to be on the expensive side. This certainly doesn't taste cheap! I am pretty picky with my coffees so I hope you will believe me when I say it is really tasty yet smooth.
Results.Title: Awesome in a jar

ClientResponses.Response:
Hi, we really value all our consumers feedback regarding the changes so thank you for getting in touch & letting us know your thoughts. We've added micro ground coffee to the recipe, to give it a more well rounded taste. This coffee is non-soluble and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee!

If the micro ground coffee isn't for you, find our 100% soluble range here: https://goo.gl/b1fPGa

Results.ReviewText:
I have been a drinker of this particular coffee for 10+ years.
and with the recent packaging change they appear to have changed the taste.
I now find the taste more bitter, and also seem to have black grit now in the bottom of my mug were i did not before.
Think it's time to find an alternative, which saddens and annoys me.
why didn't you just leave it alone.
Results.Title: They have changed it for the worse

Results.ReviewText: I have been using Nescafe Gold Blend for a long, long time - now, since you have changed the formulation I fear that it is too long.  There is a subtle and not to be forgotten taste in this that shouldn't be there.  There are dregs in the bottom of the cup; really?  After two recent weeks in Italy and France it's back to the drawing board for you and for me!
Results.Title: Factory floor dust!

ClientResponses.Response: Hey, thanks for taking the time & leaving your feedback! It saddens us to hear you're not a fan of the changes we've made but we appreciate you letting us know!

Results.ReviewText: I hope that Nescafe will soon change the Gold Blend  back to the original method. The new one is terrible. I have now got to start buyng other coffees to find one that is actually good to drink. If customers wanted to have an "espresso  based barista style coffee" then they would buy a relevant one. Why change something that worked and that everyone enjoyed.
Results.Title: Nice jar

Results.ReviewText: Bought this coffee for years and love the taste and quality. One of the best instant coffees around.  Lately however disappointed to see a film on my cup which wasn't there before and the taste is not as good either as it used to be yet still considered good quality for money! Now seem to get headaches myself from this coffee and preferred how it use to be.
Results.Title: GOLD BLEND INSTANT COFFEE

ClientResponses.Response: Thanks for letting us know your thoughts on the changes we've recently made. It's disappointing to hear you're not a fan but we'll let the rest of the team know!

Results.ReviewText: Truly awful new jar design.  Shiny and slippery, too wide to hold easily unless you have large hands.  Lid is hard work to open. The whole thing is very difficult for those of us whose hands are not young any more.  Actual coffee seems weaker than before and bland tasting.  I've used Gold Blend for years but will probably change to a different coffee now.
Results.Title: Why the dreadful new jar design?

ClientResponses.Response:
Hi, thanks for getting in touch! That's roast and ground coffee at the bottom of your cup and nothing to be alarmed by. We’ve added this to our recipe recently. For more information, watch this video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aTUCiAvWyLg&index=22&list=PLBwKOSzTG9BZFv1nKqh8ZxxTOwJaeDaT

It saddens us to hear you're not enjoying the new recipe but check out some alternative products that you could try here: https://goo.gl/xTboqP

Results.ReviewText: We are very disappointed in the new Gold Blend.  After enjoying this coffee for many years, we now find it very bland and lacking.  We definitely don't like the gritty bits left in the bottom of our cups.  Please bring back our old favourite.  In the meantime, we are on a mission to find a tasty replacement and so far Nescafe Alta Rico is getting close.
Results.Title: What has happened to Gold Blend?

Results.ReviewText: We spent years trying a different coffee each month, including freshly roasted beans, expensive variants and fancy machines, until we tried Nescafe Gold Blend. Since then we have stuck with our firm favourite and many of our friends have switched to the same, after visiting us. For consistently great taste and value for money, Gold Blend can't be beaten!
Results.Title: Great taste!

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks for getting in touch. We've added micro ground coffee to our NESCAFÉ Gold Blend recipe giving a richer aroma and a more intense roasted flavour. It's sad to hear you don't enjoy it as much but thank you for letting us know!

Results.ReviewText: I have been drinking giold blend forever but I hate the tast of the new gold blend what have u done , has it got chickery in it or something , the cost can be between £5.00 and £7.50 so its expensive , but i accept that coffee goes up and down , but its not a nice coffee to drink any more so will not be buying it again , unless u go back to original mix
Results.Title: Bitter tast  OF NEW BLEND

Results.ReviewText: I tried this last week because, well I needed something to lift my mood after a days work!  And it worked!  The tones are strong and deep and the taste hits the spot! The price point was just right and the jar should last until next week, unless I have another bad day and then I'm just going to take the jar to work so I can get m lift whenever I need it
Results.Title: More aroma than a box of roses

Results.ReviewText: I usually buy the normal Nescafe - this was on offer so i gave it a try - well  I can honestly say I am glad I did. I just love the rich smooth taste and it is so easy to have a brilliant cup of coffee at any time of the day. Necafe never fails to supply the taste and the aroma of the perfect cup of coffee. This will be on my shopping list from now on.
Results.Title: The pefect Instant coffee - full of flavour !!

Results.ReviewText: I occasionally buy gold blend which is better, I think, than 'standard' Nescafe. The main problem this that the 'freeze-dried type of granules are much slower at dissolving than standard instant coffees. I often end up with undissolved 'floaters' which is annoying. Flavour is better than 'standard'  instants, as you would expect from the higher price.
Results.Title: It's quite good for an instant coffee

ClientResponses.Response: That's disappointing to hear & we're sad you aren't enjoying the new recipe but we really appreciate your feedback. Thanks for getting in touch & letting us know.

Results.ReviewText: We have bought Gold Blend for years as we found it the best of the instant coffee on the market.  Assumed just new packaging but it is so weak we used twice as much as normal to make a half decent cup. Have found some old stock in a low cost store and will only continue with Gold Blend for as long as we can get the old stock.  Wrong move on your part!
